{"id":14881757,"mediaExerciseId":"9e471f93-6832-4148-a117-d0f144934d93","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"21.6","sectionTitle":"Exchange Rate Risk","pageNumber":731,"solutions":[{"id":5977601,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to explain the concepts of exchange rate risk.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/c7b63e3acb8e3bcc1742679e43814bc4/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/c7b63e3acb8e3bcc1742679e43814bc4/lateximg.png","width":496}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Exchange rate risk** is a risk that happens during international operations because of the changes in currency values. Therefore, managing this risk is important in the international finance.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/ea1877acd0c5ab116837871eb04bb644/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/ea1877acd0c5ab116837871eb04bb644/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"## 6a.\n\nWe are asked to determine the different types of exchange risk.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The exchange rate risk has **three** which are the following:\n1. Short-run exposure\n2. Long-run exposure\n3. Translation exposure","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/f081ef6bfa17325a11be92fcf8beab52/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/f081ef6bfa17325a11be92fcf8beab52/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**Short-run exposure** is a risk created by  the *day-to-day fluctuations* in exchange rates. **Long-run exposure** is a risk when the value of the foreign operations fluctuate because of *unexpected changes in relative economic conditions* that will cause a change in exchange rate as well. Lastly, **translation exposure** is a risk that occurs on companies that conducts business transactions outside their country and requires the *translation of the currencies* involved into the domestic currency. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":256,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/bc2e449180ed51b1775b94140211f019/lateximg_large.png","width":1057},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/bc2e449180ed51b1775b94140211f019/lateximg.png","width":530}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"## 6b.\n\nWe are asked to determine how can a firm hedge short-run and long-run exchange rate risk. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"**Short-run exposure** is a risk created by  the *day-to-day fluctuations* in exchange rates. A firm can hedge short-run exchange risk by *locking an exchange rate*. We can lock an exchange rate by entering into a forward contract.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/74768388d4f213c49c31c9f03e5bc9ab/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/74768388d4f213c49c31c9f03e5bc9ab/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"**Long-run exposure** is a risk when the value of the foreign operations fluctuate because of *unexpected changes in relative economic conditions* that will cause a change in exchange rate as well. A firm can hedge long-run exchange by *matching foreign currency inflows and outflows*. A firm can also *match foreign currency-denominated assets and liabilities*.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/8aaa6ac2ef5be2040da9d2ad3391f9f8/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/8aaa6ac2ef5be2040da9d2ad3391f9f8/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, we explained the concepts of exchange rate risk.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/9b463577ca00af184304019bf88b44e9/lateximg_large.png","width":861},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/d25c0b7eafcd4fd3ee539400f03b2419/9b463577ca00af184304019bf88b44e9/lateximg.png","width":430}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"c624d54f-6cf1-44eb-bd21-3b88ee0c3a98","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":9}],"textbook":{"authors":"B